						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying near the Śrīrāma temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1356, Īśvara, Āshāḍha, śu. [10].</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record the gift of some land (to the temple) by a certain Buḍḍinēḍu, when Siṅgarayyadēva-Mahāraja was governing Nāgārjunikoṇḍa, for the merit of his parents.</p>						

						</summary>
